The deduction rules include:
- 0.3 points for inadequate space, out of camera view, poor lighting, inaudible kihap;
- 0.6 points for pets or people entering the field, whole body not seen, portrait mode video, form switch, same generation in Family category;
- 0 score for wrong form, repeated form in K2, edited video, wrong division, political/religious displays, moving camera, single poomsae in video, and wearing incorrect attire or accessories.

Accuracy deductions include:
- 0.3 points for inadequate space, out of camera view, poor lighting, inaudible kihap;
- 0.6 points for pets or people entering the field, whole body not seen, portrait mode video, form switch, same generation in Family category;
- 0.3 points for overtime (more than 90 seconds).

Disqualification can occur due to:
- Video that has been edited or shows proof of editing;
- Submission of wrong videos to wrong division;
- Display of political, religious and non-recognized NOC flags;
- Movement of camera during performance;
- Only one taegeuk/poomsae recorded in the video;
- A colored belt competing in a poom- or black belt category.

Incorrect attire includes:
- Wearing shoes or socks;
- Wearing jewelry or wristbands;
- Wearing incorrect Dobok and incorrect belt.
